{"kind": "page", "url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "path": "en/llm-gateway.md", "title": "LLM gateway configuration", "description": "Learn how to configure Claude Code to work with LLM gateway solutions. Covers gateway requirements, authentication configuration, model selection, and provider-specific endpoint setup.", "description_source": "llms.txt", "content_hash": "e34a4d77c0d5579999a347cde6956d3e1d59f5cc81a4c642a4e673ed638b9b28", "volatile": false}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Learn how to configure Claude Code to work with LLM gateway solutions. Covers gateway requirements, authentication configuration, model selection, and provider-specific endpoint setup.\n\nLLM gateways provide a centralized proxy layer between Claude Code and model providers, often providing:\n\n- Centralized authentication - Single point for API key management\n- Usage tracking - Monitor usage across teams and projects\n- Cost controls - Implement budgets and rate limits\n- Audit logging - Track all model interactions for compliance\n- Model routing - Switch between providers without code changes", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "58803a718a532b52", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#gateway-requirements", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "Claude Code determines which features to enable based on the API format. When using the Anthropic Messages format with Bedrock or Vertex, you may need to set environment variable `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS=1`."}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "837986cb2b0e4663", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#gateway-requirements", "position": 0, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["header", "description"], "cells": ["`X-Claude-Code-Session-Id`", "A unique identifier for the current Claude Code session. Proxies can use this to aggregate all API requests from a single session without parsing the request body."]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#gateway-requirements", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "gateway-requirements", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > Gateway requirements", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "For an LLM gateway to work with Claude Code, it must meet the following requirements:\n\nAPI format\n\nThe gateway must expose to clients at least one of the following API formats:\n\n1. Anthropic Messages: `/v1/messages`, `/v1/messages/count_tokens`\n  1. Must forward request headers: `anthropic-beta`, `anthropic-version`\n3. Bedrock InvokeModel: `/invoke`, `/invoke-with-response-stream`\n  3. Must preserve request body fields: `anthropic_beta`, `anthropic_version`\n5. Vertex rawPredict: `:rawPredict`, `:streamRawPredict`, `/count-tokens:rawPredict`\n  5. Must forward request headers: `anthropic-beta`, `anthropic-version`\n\nFailure to forward headers or preserve body fields may result in reduced functionality or inability to use Claude Code features.\n\nRequest headers\n\nClaude Code includes the following headers on every API request:\n\nClaude Code also prepends a short attribution block to the system prompt containing the client version and a fingerprint derived from the conversation. The Anthropic API strips this block before processing, so it does not affect first-party prompt caching. If your gateway implements its own prompt cache keyed on the full request body, set `CLAUDE_CODE_ATTRIBUTION_HEADER=0` to omit it.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#model-selection", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "model-selection", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > Configuration > Model selection", "level": 3, "position": 3, "text": "By default, Claude Code will use standard model names for the selected API format.\n\nIf you have configured custom model names in your gateway, use the environment variables documented in Model configuration to match your custom names.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#configuration", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#configuration", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "configuration", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > Configuration", "level": 2, "position": 2, "text": "", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "885ca3f469ff0ea4", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#litellm-configuration", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "warning", "text": "LiteLLM PyPI versions 1.82.7 and 1.82.8 were compromised with credential-stealing malware. Do not install these versions. If you have already installed them:\n\n- Remove the package\n- Rotate all credentials on affected systems\n- Follow the remediation steps in BerriAI/litellm#24518\n\nLiteLLM is a third-party proxy service. Anthropic doesn't endorse, maintain, or audit LiteLLM's security or functionality. This guide is provided for informational purposes and may become outdated. Use at your own discretion."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#prerequisites", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "prerequisites", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > LiteLLM configuration > Prerequisites", "level": 3, "position": 5, "text": "- Claude Code updated to the latest version\n- LiteLLM Proxy Server deployed and accessible\n- Access to Claude models through your chosen provider", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#litellm-configuration", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "40dabd950c7e92c4", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#static-api-key", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "# Set in environment\nexport ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-litellm-static-key\n\n# Or in Claude Code settings\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"sk-litellm-static-key\"\n  }\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "Simplest method using a fixed API key:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#static-api-key", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "static-api-key", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > LiteLLM configuration > Basic LiteLLM setup > Authentication methods > Static API key", "level": 5, "position": 8, "text": "Simplest method using a fixed API key:\n\nThis value will be sent as the `Authorization` header.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#authentication-methods", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "bfa2993b670c8149", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#dynamic-api-key-with-helper", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "#!/bin/bash\n# ~/bin/get-litellm-key.sh\n\n# Example: Fetch key from vault\nvault kv get -field=api_key secret/litellm/claude-code\n\n# Example: Generate JWT token\njwt encode \\\n  --secret=\"${JWT_SECRET}\" \\\n  --exp=\"+1h\" \\\n  '{\"user\":\"'${USER}'\",\"team\":\"engineering\"}'", "preceding_paragraph": "1. Create an API key helper script:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "4857b0c13b2cdb76", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#dynamic-api-key-with-helper", "position": 1, "language": "json", "text": "{\n  \"apiKeyHelper\": \"~/bin/get-litellm-key.sh\"\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "1. Configure Claude Code settings to use the helper:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "84fbf616965d37d1", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#dynamic-api-key-with-helper", "position": 2, "language": "bash", "text": "# Refresh every hour (3600000 ms)\nexport CLAUDE_CODE_API_KEY_HELPER_TTL_MS=3600000", "preceding_paragraph": "1. Set token refresh interval:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#dynamic-api-key-with-helper", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md", "anchor": "dynamic-api-key-with-helper", "breadcrumb": "LLM gateway configuration > LiteLLM configuration > Basic LiteLLM setup > Authentication methods > Dynamic API key with helper", "level": 5, "position": 9, "text": "For rotating keys or per-user authentication:\n\n1. Create an API key helper script:\n\n1. Configure Claude Code settings to use the helper:\n\n1. Set token refresh interval:\n\nThis value will be sent as `Authorization` and `X-Api-Key` headers. The `apiKeyHelper` has lower precedence than `ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN` or `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway.md#authentication-methods", "external_links": []}
